1
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,399
I don't like you doing this here.

2
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:42,600
Where should we do it, then, Samu?

3
00:00:42,679 --> 00:00:44,560
What if the cops catch us?

4
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,920
Why would the cops show up here?

5
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:49,320
We're three innocent schoolkids.

6
00:00:52,159 --> 00:00:55,000
-Your mother's in jail because of this.
-Wrong.

7
00:00:55,119 --> 00:00:57,799
She's in jail because some son of a bitch
sold us out.

8
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,960
But this is different.
We're like family here.

9
00:01:05,359 --> 00:01:06,879
Fine, but it stays here.

10
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:10,599
Not a word to anyone. OK? Anyone.

11
00:01:11,599 --> 00:01:13,680
Relax, we know what we're doing.

12
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:31,000
Keep it up, Valerio.

13
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,479
I can't believe it!

14
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,719
Good. You finally learned how to cheat.

15
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,680
I don't cheat, sweetheart.

16
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:39,159
The thing is, I'm... one of a kind.

17
00:02:39,319 --> 00:02:41,240
And I have great study buddies.

18
00:02:41,319 --> 00:02:43,639
We go at it hard every afternoon...

19
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,199
and every night, too.

20
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,960
You're kidding, right?

21
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,759
No, I don't think so.

22
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,080
This is serious... very serious.

23
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,159
B+

24
00:03:18,759 --> 00:03:20,199
-No, it's his turn.
-Stop!

25
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,560
-Quiet. Which one was it?
-It tickles!

26
00:03:22,639 --> 00:03:25,319
What? OK, potassium nitrate.

27
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,319
-What?
-Take something off.

28
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:30,960
What do you mean?
He got it right, didn't he?

29
00:03:31,039 --> 00:03:34,560
-Yes, but he's wearing too much clothing.
-This girl learns fast.

30
00:03:34,639 --> 00:03:38,159
-Not as fast as you.
-Oh, really? Not as fast as me?

31
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,680
Show some respect. I'm the teacher here.

32
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:45,639
I never thought
studying could be so much fun.

33
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:49,439
Do you realize you could even graduate
if you want to?

34
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,400
You could even go to university.

35
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:54,080
-For real.
-I don't know.

36
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:55,879
I never thought about my future.

37
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:58,680
In fact, it never occurred to me
I could have one.

38
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,319
Well, you could.

39
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:03,719
You're going to London, right?

40
00:04:04,599 --> 00:04:05,840
King's College.

41
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,159
Why don't you join us?

42
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:11,120
No way! I don't have the grades

43
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:13,520
or the money to get
into a place like that.

44
00:04:13,599 --> 00:04:15,439
Neither do I, but his mothers will...

45
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:18,600
-We got in with our connections.
-Yeah.

46
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:21,279
My mothers are friends with the dean.

47
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,360
-Really?
-Yes.

48
00:04:23,759 --> 00:04:25,480
I don't suppose they could...

49
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,000
Well...

50
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:30,959
my mothers are vouching
for Cayetana because...

51
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:33,800
well, because she's my girlfriend.

52
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:36,680
I'm not saying that we're not a couple...

53
00:04:37,399 --> 00:04:41,079
but they know her better, longer.
They don't know who you are yet.

54
00:04:42,079 --> 00:04:44,199
-So, I'm nobody, right?
-I didn't say that.

55
00:04:44,279 --> 00:04:45,560
-No.
-You misunderstood.

56
00:04:45,639 --> 00:04:48,160
-It's OK.
-I didn't mean that.

57
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,959
There's a word
for what you two have, but...

58
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,199
there's no word for this.

59
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:57,000
Don't worry.
You've done enough for me.

60
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,199
Hey, it's fine.

61
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:15,160
Gin and tonic, please.

62
00:05:18,639 --> 00:05:20,199
What's this blackout thing about?

63
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,519
A blackout, it's just that.

64
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:26,000
This Friday at midnight, 
it's lights out at the club.

65
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,079
That's it?

66
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,639
People dig the dark.

67
00:05:30,319 --> 00:05:32,839
They can do what they want
without being seen.

68
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:37,639
You could fuck three guys 
right under Nadia's nose.

69
00:05:39,199 --> 00:05:42,639
I'd be happy if you didn't say anything.
It's better for her.

70
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,160
It's better for her to live a lie?

71
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:49,959
If she finds out, she might break up
with me and forget all about New York.

72
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,120
Why risk it?

73
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:56,680
That's what I'm thinking.
Why did you take that risk?

74
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,560
Why'd you kiss me?

75
00:05:59,079 --> 00:06:00,519
Why do you think I did?

76
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:05,519
I'm with someone, too.
But my relationship is actually real.

77
00:06:09,639 --> 00:06:10,480
Are you happy?

78
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:13,279
Yes.

79
00:06:13,839 --> 00:06:14,839
Sure.

80
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:18,399
I see Nadia isn't the only one
living a lie.

81
00:06:19,399 --> 00:06:20,360
It's on the house.

82
00:06:40,199 --> 00:06:41,639
Your hands are freezing.

83
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,439
It's OK. It's no big deal.

84
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:07,920
You didn't see your face.

85
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,000
Ander...

86
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,279
Please don't say it's no big deal.

87
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:16,040
It is.

88
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,120
Chemo's fucking me up...

89
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:21,839
and I'm scared.

90
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:24,399
And so are you.

91
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:30,879
Maybe we should stop acting
like it's no big deal.

92
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:53,120
Lucrecia, do you have a minute?
It's about Columbia.

93
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,519
Take a seat.

94
00:08:02,639 --> 00:08:05,800
I wanted to tell you that both of you got
the highest possible grade.

95
00:08:05,879 --> 00:08:10,000
We have to ask you to make one last effort
so the jury can make a decision.

96
00:08:10,079 --> 00:08:13,600
Next Wednesday,
you'll need to do an oral presentation

97
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,319
that goes into more detail
on the last topic you addressed.

98
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,720
So? Pretty, huh?

99
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,480
Hey! Wow!

100
00:08:30,279 --> 00:08:31,279
It's the chemo.

101
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:33,360
I have cancer.

102
00:08:42,279 --> 00:08:45,519
I'm sure you have lots of questions,
but that's what Wikipedia's for.

103
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,039
I get tired real quick.

104
00:08:56,519 --> 00:08:57,440
I hated him.

105
00:08:57,919 --> 00:08:59,720
I blamed him for my illness.

106
00:09:03,639 --> 00:09:05,320
The champagne bottle broke.

107
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:09,559
The neck fell by the bathroom,
and I went to pick it up to throw it out.

108
00:09:11,279 --> 00:09:12,320
Polo was there.

109
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:16,320
What are you talking about?

110
00:09:17,159 --> 00:09:18,879
I couldn't hold back.

111
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:21,759
I stabbed him in the heart with the glass.

112
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:24,720
You're nuts. Why would you confess?

113
00:09:24,919 --> 00:09:25,879
What's it matter?

114
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:29,759
I'm almost dead.

115
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,840
I won't let you destroy yourself
to protect someone.

116
00:09:35,279 --> 00:09:36,759
How long has he been sick?

117
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:37,759
For months.

118
00:09:38,759 --> 00:09:40,159
I found out recently, too.

119
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,759
What do the doctors say?

120
00:09:42,159 --> 00:09:43,000
Not much.

121
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:46,039
His chemo's almost over,
and we'll see after that.

122
00:09:46,639 --> 00:09:48,240
But he'll make it, right?

123
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,080
Of course he will.

124
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:52,799
It's Ander.

125
00:09:55,519 --> 00:09:56,720
He doesn't deserve this.

126
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:00,279
Not everyone gets what they deserve.

127
00:10:12,399 --> 00:10:13,480
You knew, right?

128
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:19,279
Do you think I didn't want to tell you?

129
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,639
That I wanted to deal with this alone?

130
00:10:22,279 --> 00:10:25,480
-So why didn't you?
-Ander asked me to keep it a secret.

131
00:10:27,279 --> 00:10:30,159
And I thought, what was the point
of telling you?

132
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,279
You'd cure him?

133
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:32,720
Besides...

134
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,600
sometimes, the truth is...

135
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,240
useless.

136
00:10:41,159 --> 00:10:42,200
Forgive me.

137
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:46,000
And thanks... for everything.

138
00:10:46,759 --> 00:10:49,080
You're the best thing I've got, Samu.
And the only--

139
00:10:49,159 --> 00:10:51,720
-Don't talk nonsense.
-No, I really mean it.

140
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:56,399
We've turned your house into a lab,
and you just grin and bear it.

141
00:10:57,080 --> 00:11:00,279
As soon as this batch is done,
I promise you it'll be over.

142
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,039
We'll close the business.

143
00:11:02,519 --> 00:11:04,519
Then you and I will have
a very boring life.

144
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,159
I'd really like that.

145
00:11:23,879 --> 00:11:25,240
We just found out.

146
00:11:26,799 --> 00:11:27,679
What a bummer.

147
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,919
He's tired of hiding it.

148
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:34,080
It's taking longer than we expected.

149
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,279
And how are you doing? 

150
00:11:38,159 --> 00:11:40,519
Never mind me. What matters now is him.

151
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,840
I try to get him to go out, have fun,
forget everything, but...

152
00:11:48,519 --> 00:11:51,200
He's very lucky to have you by his side,
you know?

153
00:11:52,159 --> 00:11:53,480
If you only knew.

154
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:55,960
I know.

155
00:11:57,559 --> 00:11:58,840
A word of advice.

156
00:11:58,919 --> 00:12:02,159
If you want to keep your romance a secret,
you should be more discreet.

157
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,840
But relax, I won't say a word.

158
00:12:03,919 --> 00:12:06,960
There's no secret romance, damn it. 
He's my sister's boyfriend.

159
00:12:07,039 --> 00:12:09,080
Yeah... Heavy, huh?

160
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:13,919
Look, being cheated on
makes us... stronger.

161
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:15,879
See it that way.

162
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:20,320
I know because my boyfriend
cheated on me with your sister.

163
00:12:21,799 --> 00:12:24,159
-When are you going to tell her?
-Never.

164
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:26,039
Nadia can't leave Malick.

165
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:30,039
-Why?
-She needs him to go to New York.

166
00:12:30,559 --> 00:12:32,320
He'll be there next year too.

167
00:12:32,399 --> 00:12:34,600
That's why my dad let her apply
for the grant.

168
00:12:35,279 --> 00:12:39,279
If she found out he's using her
as a beard, she'd scrap the whole thing.

169
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:49,080
-The contract has arrived.
-Has it?

170
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,360
When will it be signed?

171
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:55,120
It's with the lawyers now.
It will take a few days.

172
00:12:56,279 --> 00:12:57,519
The only thing is...

173
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:00,919
there's a clause
that allows Yeray to withdraw the funding

174
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:03,519
-at any time during the first five years.
-What?

175
00:13:04,279 --> 00:13:06,879
He'll be pulling our strings 
the entire time.

176
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,039
Five years?

177
00:13:08,879 --> 00:13:11,159
-I'm going to tell that bastard off.
-No.

178
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:15,000
You won't say a word.

179
00:13:16,159 --> 00:13:17,720
Now more than ever.

180
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,600
WE HAVE TO CELEBRATE TONIGHT, RIGHT?

181
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,279
Have fun.

182
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:32,080
Hi. I'm looking for--

183
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:37,840
this book.

184
00:13:38,799 --> 00:13:39,960
Sorry, I've got it.

185
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:45,320
Nadia... you know it's essential
for the presentation,

186
00:13:45,399 --> 00:13:46,639
and it's not online.

187
00:13:47,639 --> 00:13:48,600
Well, I've got it.

188
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:54,559
I need to ask you a question.

189
00:13:56,279 --> 00:13:59,279
If you knew someone was being cheated on,
would you tell them?

190
00:14:06,799 --> 00:14:07,639
I'm sorry.

191
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,679
I never apologized to you
for what happened.

192
00:14:16,679 --> 00:14:17,600
Why now?

193
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:23,960
Because... you never know
how much time we have left in this world.

194
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,519
And now that...

195
00:14:28,279 --> 00:14:30,360
I'm starting something serious
with someone,

196
00:14:30,879 --> 00:14:32,639
I understand you better than ever.

197
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:37,279
I always thought
you were cold and heartless...

198
00:14:38,279 --> 00:14:40,799
until I helped break your heart
into a thousand pieces.

199
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:43,600
I'm really sorry, Lu.

200
00:14:47,639 --> 00:14:49,080
I'm done with the book.

201
00:14:56,399 --> 00:14:57,399
-What's up?
-Nothing.

202
00:14:59,879 --> 00:15:01,600
Is that what you wanted to talk about?

203
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,879
Or is someone else cheating?

204
00:15:04,519 --> 00:15:05,360
No, no one.

205
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,240
Forget about it.

206
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:14,840
How are you?

207
00:15:15,759 --> 00:15:16,600
Fine.

208
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:23,320
So...

209
00:15:24,279 --> 00:15:26,960
are you training hard?
With the punching bag?

210
00:15:28,399 --> 00:15:30,639
Do we have to speak in Morse code?

211
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:32,200
You've got to be kidding me.

212
00:15:32,279 --> 00:15:34,399
You need to be careful here, honey.

213
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:36,519
You should've taken your own advice.

214
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,200
I don't trust a soul.

215
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,600
What a sad life.
I don't want that for myself.

216
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:45,440
-Well, it's the one you're leading now.
-Yeah.

217
00:15:46,039 --> 00:15:49,000
Until I get the money I need
to pay off the school.

218
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,279
Then, to hell with it.

219
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,799
You'll always need more.

220
00:15:53,039 --> 00:15:55,279
Or do you think
once you've tasted seafood,

221
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:57,759
you can go back to eating canned sardines?

222
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,039
You should fucking know by now,

223
00:16:02,159 --> 00:16:05,240
every shrimp I'll eat
will be paid for with my own work.

224
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:07,000
No hustling and no scumbags.

225
00:16:08,039 --> 00:16:08,919
I'm done.

226
00:16:09,879 --> 00:16:12,159
You can see the scumbags coming
a mile away.

227
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:15,639
It's the good guys,
the ones who look like angels...

228
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,279
Those are the ones
you have to look out for.

229
00:16:25,919 --> 00:16:27,840
What the fuck's that mean?

230
00:16:27,919 --> 00:16:28,879
What I mean...

231
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:31,600
is that our living room was bugged.

232
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:35,320
And all the “scumbags”
were taken down to the police station

233
00:16:35,399 --> 00:16:36,879
or are sitting in jail.

234
00:16:38,159 --> 00:16:39,159
All except one.

235
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:41,600
The little angel.

236
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:48,200
No... Samu would never do that to me.

237
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:51,080
-How do you know?
-Because he loves me.

238
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,440
Do you know what that means?

239
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:57,120
What if you could make sure?

240
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,919
Samu, I need to find out
who stabbed us in the back.

241
00:17:03,519 --> 00:17:05,720
You can't imagine how badly I need that.

242
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,599
Didn't we want a boring life
with no trouble?

243
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:11,079
Are you with me or not?

244
00:17:18,319 --> 00:17:21,000
The snitch must've been recorded
by the security cameras.

245
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:23,720
We had them everywhere,
but they were taken away.

246
00:17:23,799 --> 00:17:27,319
The security company
might have a copy of everything.

247
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:30,039
But my mom doesn't know
which company we had.

248
00:17:30,119 --> 00:17:33,039
The police seized everything.
Contracts, invoices...

249
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:35,720
Two months ago,
a camera broke, and I kept it.

250
00:17:35,799 --> 00:17:38,599
It should have a sticker
with the company's details.

251
00:17:39,319 --> 00:17:41,279
Why would they give you a copy?

252
00:17:41,359 --> 00:17:43,519
Because everyone has a price.

253
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,039
Look over there.

254
00:18:01,319 --> 00:18:02,160
It's here.

255
00:18:10,559 --> 00:18:12,279
Fuck, there's nothing on it.

256
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:21,200
You could try calling
all the security companies in the country

257
00:18:21,319 --> 00:18:22,640
to see if you were clients.

258
00:18:23,559 --> 00:18:25,480
But I think that's confidential.

259
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,519
