Didn't your parents say that
when you said you liked girls?

377
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:29,720
That's enough, Polo!
It's always a struggle with you.

378
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:33,559
Don't we have enough problems already? 
And now this?

379
00:26:54,759 --> 00:26:55,599
Hey.

380
00:26:55,759 --> 00:26:56,599
Hi.

381
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,319
It suits you.

382
00:27:07,319 --> 00:27:10,279
Listen, if you need anything,
anything at all...

383
00:27:10,839 --> 00:27:14,680
I won't shave my hair off
for moral support, but anything else...

384
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:16,519
Thanks.

385
00:27:17,279 --> 00:27:21,559
I'm fed up with all the sad looks.
I don't know what's worse, chemo or pity.

386
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:23,160
Pity, for sure.

387
00:27:24,799 --> 00:27:26,400
But it's not all bad.

388
00:27:26,559 --> 00:27:28,480
Cancer has an upside too.

389
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,880
Really? Like what?

390
00:27:35,519 --> 00:27:39,400
Well... I don't know.
I used to feel overwhelmed with life.

391
00:27:40,079 --> 00:27:42,480
My future, my parents on top of me...

392
00:27:44,519 --> 00:27:48,240
