435
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:31,960
Polo's mothers might be lesbians,
but they're older.

436
00:30:32,799 --> 00:30:33,640
OK?

437
00:30:34,039 --> 00:30:35,240
They don't get it.

438
00:30:36,039 --> 00:30:38,319
I don't get it either, to be honest.

439
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:41,440
I'm not going to pretend
I'm modern, but...

440
00:30:42,039 --> 00:30:46,359
girls don't dream of having
a white wedding with two grooms, you know?

441
00:30:46,559 --> 00:30:48,440
It's not what we were taught.

442
00:30:51,319 --> 00:30:53,119
I used to think...

443
00:30:53,319 --> 00:30:56,480
that people were like halves
trying to make a whole.

444
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:58,440
Or like nuts and bolts.

445
00:30:58,519 --> 00:31:00,960
All you had to do was find
the one that...

446
00:31:01,279 --> 00:31:03,079
fit you perfectly.

447
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:08,880
But Polo and I didn't fit together before.

448
00:31:10,319 --> 00:31:11,720
Then you showed up...

449
00:31:13,119 --> 00:31:14,920
and now we fit together.

450
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:21,279
You're the piece that we were missing.

451
00:31:24,359 --> 00:31:25,200
And, hell...

452
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:30,599
when you find love,
it sucks to have to let it go.

453
00:31:40,759 --> 00:31:42,359
Guzmán, are you coming?

454
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:45,279
Omar wants me to go
so that I'm not alone all day.

455
00:31:45,359 --> 00:31:46,839
What about your friend Polo?

456
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:53,079
I saw you last night.
You were having a blast.

457
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:54,880
