is turning your hobby into a job,

527
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:28,599
so, congrats.

528
00:37:28,679 --> 00:37:31,320
It's a job... and also a secret.

529
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,880
Can you keep it?

530
00:37:35,519 --> 00:37:37,199
I can make it worth the effort.

531
00:37:38,679 --> 00:37:40,920
Wrong person. That's not my thing.

532
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,760
And what is your thing?

533
00:37:43,199 --> 00:37:44,440
What do you need?

534
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,559
I just need to fall in love.

535
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:55,320
Boom! I have just the thing for that.

536
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:59,000
This is... happiness...

537
00:38:00,079 --> 00:38:00,920
and love.

538
00:38:25,639 --> 00:38:26,480
How are you?

539
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:32,679
It's fine, go home. Don't stay for me.

540
00:38:34,039 --> 00:38:35,599
Will you be up when I get home?

541
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:38,639
I can't dance, let alone fuck.

542
00:38:41,519 --> 00:38:43,199
That's not what I meant, but it's OK.

543
00:38:45,119 --> 00:38:46,079
It's not OK.

544
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:49,159
We should admit that, too.

545
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:51,760
Listen...

546
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:54,519
I don't care if you see other people.

547
00:38:54,599 --> 00:38:56,159
Why are you saying that?

548
00:38:58,159 --> 00:38:59,400
It's not normal...

549
00:39:01,199 --> 00:39:02,440
but I want you to be happy.

550
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:04,440
You're bitter because of me.

551
00:39:05,079 --> 00:39:06,400
You think I like that?

552
00:39:08,199 --> 00:39:10,320
No... I don't understand, Ander.

553
00:39:13,239 --> 00:39:14,480
It's fine, forget it.

554
00:39:34,039 --> 00:39:36,320
Watch this for me.
I'm going to the bathroom.

555
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:53,280
Omar, throw this in the trash
without being seen.

556
00:39:54,119 --> 00:39:55,440
-What?
-Trust me.

557
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:56,639
Go, damn it!

558
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:57,800
OK.

559
00:40:44,079 --> 00:40:45,000
What's up?

560
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:47,239
I just...

561
00:40:48,039 --> 00:40:50,760
I just remembered
that I lost your toothbrush.

562
00:40:51,119 --> 00:40:52,280
Can you buy me a new one?

563
00:40:52,719 --> 00:40:53,559
Of course.

564
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,800
No... Buy me thousands...

565
00:40:56,119 --> 00:40:57,880
Millions of toothbrushes!

566
00:41:10,639 --> 00:41:13,920
Sorry. The bathroom was as crowded
as the Tokyo metro.

567
00:41:16,559 --> 00:41:17,760
-Another drink?
-Yes.

568
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:20,159
Shit.

569
00:41:20,519 --> 00:41:22,320
-What's wrong?
-Where's my bag?

570
00:41:22,559 --> 00:41:23,400
Shit!

571
00:41:23,519 --> 00:41:24,679
Fucking hell!

572
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:26,039
I'm sorry, Rebe.

573
00:41:26,119 --> 00:41:28,039
The one fucking favor I ask you!

574
00:41:55,679 --> 00:41:56,519
Take this.

575
00:41:58,599 --> 00:41:59,679
Do you want me?

576
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:01,119
What?

577
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,039
Do you want to fuck?

578
00:42:04,920 --> 00:42:05,960
What about Ander?

579
00:42:06,719 --> 00:42:07,880
Ander's not here.

580
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:30,159
Right on time.

581
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:31,639
Nadia!

582
00:42:32,719 --> 00:42:33,719
Hi! Over here!

583
00:42:36,960 --> 00:42:38,039
What're you doing here?

584
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:39,400
Great hair!

585
00:42:39,519 --> 00:42:42,000
Shouldn't you be preparing
a presentation?

586
00:42:42,079 --> 00:42:44,599
I should be, but I couldn't concentrate.

587
00:42:45,039 --> 00:42:45,960
What about you?

588
00:42:46,119 --> 00:42:46,960
Want a sip?

589
00:42:47,239 --> 00:42:48,079
No.

590
00:42:48,159 --> 00:42:51,119
Me? Same as always,
I just needed... to relax.

591
00:42:52,280 --> 00:42:54,199
-You do seem a little tense.
-No!

592
00:42:54,639 --> 00:42:55,920
Have you seen Malick?

593
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,519
Yes! He's downstairs...

594
00:42:59,599 --> 00:43:01,719
dancing with the plebes.

595
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:03,320
-Thanks.
-Yup.

596
00:43:17,719 --> 00:43:20,679
So nice to see you!
I thought you'd miss the blackout!

597
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:24,119
-How come you look so happy?
-Well... 

598
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:28,519
I'm about to have enough cash
to apply to a university in London!

599
00:43:29,159 --> 00:43:30,000
What?

600
00:43:30,079 --> 00:43:33,639
It's amazing what my family will do
to keep me as far away as possible.

601
00:43:34,199 --> 00:43:36,679
You're coming with us? Yeah!

602
00:43:36,760 --> 00:43:39,039
-Really? Awesome!
-That's great!

603
00:43:39,119 --> 00:43:41,199
I couldn't let you get away.

604
00:44:01,239 --> 00:44:02,400
Where were you?

605
00:44:02,480 --> 00:44:03,800
I was looking for you!

606
00:44:04,559 --> 00:44:05,400
Here.

607
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:07,400
Weren't you staying in?

608
00:44:08,239 --> 00:44:10,119
Malick, is there anything I should know?

609
00:44:10,880 --> 00:44:12,079
Is there another girl?

610
00:44:12,159 --> 00:44:13,679
No! What're you talking about?

611
00:44:14,719 --> 00:44:15,920
So we're good?

612
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:17,400
Of course.

613
00:44:17,880 --> 00:44:20,519
I was going to tell you tomorrow,
my parents are coming.

614
00:44:20,599 --> 00:44:22,280
They want to meet you.

615
00:44:26,719 --> 00:44:29,199
-Why don't we go home now?
-No, wait.

616
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:31,519
It's time for the blackout.

617
00:44:31,599 --> 00:44:32,440
So what?

618
00:44:32,519 --> 00:44:35,760
...nine, eight, seven...

619
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:37,119
Samu, do you love me?

620
00:44:37,199 --> 00:44:38,280
What?

621
00:44:38,960 --> 00:44:41,480
...four, three, two...

622
00:44:41,559 --> 00:44:43,119
Do you love me?

623
00:44:43,199 --> 00:44:44,239
Of course I do.

624
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:01,360
I love you!

625
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:04,039
I love you too!

626
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:09,679
I had to make sure.

627
00:45:17,599 --> 00:45:18,440
What's this?

628
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:23,800
It's called fluorescent paint.

629
00:45:25,599 --> 00:45:27,360
My bag was soaked in it.

630
00:45:30,159 --> 00:45:31,079
What's that?

631
00:45:55,239 --> 00:45:56,599
Nadia!

632
00:46:01,840 --> 00:46:03,920
The security cameras didn't work.

633
00:46:04,679 --> 00:46:07,559
That kid wasn't a security guard,
and the hard drive was empty.

634
00:46:07,639 --> 00:46:10,280
-Rebeka, listen to me, please.
-No, you listen to me!

635
00:46:11,559 --> 00:46:12,840
Tell me one thing...

636
00:46:14,599 --> 00:46:16,800
-Did you get close to me just for that?
-No.

637
00:46:18,320 --> 00:46:19,639
Was it all a lie?

638
00:47:02,559 --> 00:47:03,400
Hey.

639
00:47:06,159 --> 00:47:07,000
I'm sorry.

640
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:10,639
You knew. Why didn't you tell me?

641
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:15,199
Because I didn't want to give you
an excuse to leave the competition,

642
00:47:15,280 --> 00:47:17,199
just when I'm about to win.

643
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:20,280
Do you think I'll go with him
to New York?

644
00:47:20,800 --> 00:47:22,719
Listen... with a bit of luck...

645
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:26,360
you'll have guys coming
in and out of your life.

646
00:47:26,719 --> 00:47:29,559
But an opportunity like this
only comes along once.

647
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:31,960
Plus, he used you.

648
00:47:33,199 --> 00:47:35,639
Basically, you should use him too.

649
00:47:36,960 --> 00:47:38,599
What he did hurts a lot.

650
00:47:39,719 --> 00:47:40,840
Yeah, I know.

651
00:47:42,280 --> 00:47:45,599
You had this idea of building
something amazing with him

652
00:47:45,679 --> 00:47:48,039
and living happily ever after, but no.

653
00:47:50,599 --> 00:47:54,239
And we both know he's not the boy
you're really in love with.

654
00:48:05,519 --> 00:48:06,360
Nadia.

655
00:48:07,440 --> 00:48:08,840
Speak of the devil...

656
00:48:17,079 --> 00:48:18,599
I'll meet your parents...

657
00:48:19,199 --> 00:48:21,480
but I can't promise
I'll be as good at lying...

658
00:48:22,480 --> 00:48:25,960
cheating, and pretending
that I have feelings for someone.

659
00:48:43,400 --> 00:48:44,840
This is taking too long.

660
00:48:52,400 --> 00:48:53,280
What'd you say?

661
00:48:59,079 --> 00:49:00,559
You did the right thing.

662
00:49:02,559 --> 00:49:03,679
Hey...

663
00:49:04,519 --> 00:49:05,920
You did what you had to do.

664
00:51:24,480 --> 00:51:28,320
Subtitle translation by Toni Navarro

